sequenceDiagram
    actor User as User Browser
    participant FE as Frontend (Port 3000)
    participant BE as Backend (Port 8080)
    participant GH as GitHub OAuth Server

    User->>FE: Clicks "Sign in with GitHub"
    FE->>User: Redirects to backend:<br/>http://localhost:8080/oauth2/authorization/github
    User->>BE: GET /oauth2/authorization/github
    BE->>User: Redirects (302) to GitHub login page with Client ID & Scopes
    User->>GH: User enters GitHub credentials & approves app
    GH->>User: Redirects (302) back to backend with temp 'code'
    User->>BE: GET /login/oauth2/code/github?code=XYZ
    BE->>GH: Exchanges 'code' + Client Secret for GitHub Access Token (Server-to-Server)
    GH->>BE: Returns GitHub Access Token
    BE->>BE: Saves user info & GitHub Token in Postgres database
    BE->>BE: Generates our custom app JWT token
    BE->>User: Redirects (302) to Frontend Auth Callback:<br/>http://localhost:3000/auth/callback?token=JWT
    User->>FE: Load Auth Callback Page
    FE->>FE: Save JWT token (LocalStorage/Cookie)
    FE->>User: Redirects to /dashboard
